5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to the Department of Commerce; to amend
10 Sections 41-29-282 and 41-4-126, Code of Alabama 1975, to
11 provide that the Alabama Industrial Development Training
12 Institute (AIDT) within the Department of Commerce is exempt
13 from the state procurement law and review by the Contract
14 Review Permanent Legislative Oversight Committee.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
16 Section 1. Sections 41-29-282 and 41-4-126, Code of
17 Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
18 "§41-29-282
19 (a) AIDT shall operate as a division of the Department
20 of Commerce. All of the powers, authority, duties, functions,
21 policies, and funds of, and appropriations to AIDT previously
22 conferred upon or granted to AIDT reporting to the State Board
23 of Education through the Division of Vocational-Technical
24 Education or by Alabama Executive Order No. 2012-31 are
25 confirmed, ratified, continued, transferred to, and vested in
26 AIDT.
27 (b) All contracts, leases, grants, and agreements
28 previously entered by AIDT shall continue in full force and
Page 1

previously entered by AIDT shall continue in full force and
